Popular Afro pop singer Naira Marley has revealed why he quit watching football. According to the Marlian Records boss, he lost interest to watch football because of Nigeria and Arsenal. He made the disclosure on Twitter while reacting to Nigeria’s elimination from the ongoing 2021 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) in Cameroon where they lost to Tunisia at the qualifying stage of the game. “This is why I don’t watch football anymore because of Nigeria and fucking Arsenal,” he tweeted.   I miss bachelorhood, says D’banj     Nine Yoruba actors/actresses who remarried     Nollywood star Stella Damasus loses mother   - Advertisement - In accompanying tweets, the “Soapy” singer also blamed the referee and the opposing team for Nigeria’s loss. “From when I saw a player called Ifa in the Tunisian team, I knew we weren’t gonna win. Referee head come be like orunmila,” Marley tweeted. “Referee didn’t give us that corner, he didn’t give us penalty for that handball but he wanna check VAR to give us red card kmft. Fuck football man.”